                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, Aug. 2 (PTI): Delhi High Court today directed the Municipal Council of Delhi to pay Rs 5 lakh to the wife of a bureaucrat who lost his life after falling into an uncovered pit, and form a taskforce to ensure compliance with safety norms during construction.          
	Trilok Nath Makan, 78, who had retired as additional private secretary to former Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee, fell into the pit during an evening walk on August 28, 2009, in south Delhi.                  
	 Tamluk: Nearly 500 Citu-affiliated contract labourers at the Tata Steel-owned Hooghly Met Coke and Power Co. Ltd in Haldia called an indefinite strike from Monday. They demand that half of the unloading of coals from wagons be done manually. Currently, most of the coal is unloaded with tripplers.
                                                                                                                                              
